From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: buildroot <buildroot@buildroot.org>
Date: Mon, 19 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] modules/NE10_init.c: add missing ne10_init_physics
 declaration

ne10_init_physics() is called in ne10_init() when NE10_ENABLE_PHYSICS
is defined, but the function prototype is not exposed in any public
header — it is only defined in NE10_init_physics.c. This causes an
implicit function declaration error with modern GCC (which defaults
to -Werror=implicit-function-declaration).

Add a forward declaration guarded by the same NE10_ENABLE_PHYSICS
preprocessor conditional.

Signed-off-by: buildroot <buildroot@buildroot.org>
---
 modules/NE10_init.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/modules/NE10_init.c b/modules/NE10_init.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/modules/NE10_init.c
+++ b/modules/NE10_init.c
@@ -31,6 +31,10 @@
 
 #include "NE10.h"
 
+#if defined(NE10_ENABLE_PHYSICS)
+extern ne10_result_t ne10_init_physics(ne10_int32_t is_NEON_available);
+#endif
+
 #define CPUINFO_BUFFER_SIZE  (1024*4)
 
 // This local variable indicates whether or not the running platform supports ARM NEON
